What is OCD..?

Obsessive-Compulsive Disorder (OCD) is characterized by the presence of persistent obsessions or compulsions, or most commonly both. Obsessions are repetitive and persistent thoughts, images, or impulses/urges that are intrusive, unwanted, and commonly associated with anxiety. Compulsions are repetitive behaviors, including mental acts, that the individual feels driven to perform in response to an obsession, according to rigid rules, or to achieve a sense of completeness. For a diagnosis, these symptoms must be time-consuming or cause significant distress or impairment in important areas of functioning
